verses.text:
Thou hast ravished my heart, my sister, \add my\add* spouse;
thou hast ravished my heart with one of thine eyes, with one chain
of thy neck.\f + \fr 4.9  \ft ravished: or, taken away\f*

A garden inclosed \add is\add* my sister, \add my\add* spouse;
a spring shut up, a fountain sealed. \f + \fr 4.12  \ft inclosed: Heb.
barred\f*\f + \fr 4.12  \ft shut up: Heb. barred\f*

I said, I will go up to the palm tree, I will take hold of the
boughs thereof: now also thy breasts shall be as clusters of the
vine, and the smell of thy nose like apples;
